{"title":"Articles: A, An, The","type":"quiz","level":"A1","category":"Grammatica","desc":"Quando usare gli articoli indeterminativi e quello determinativo.","points":30,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"She is ___ engineer.","opts":["a","an","the","--"],"correct":1,"expl":"\"engineer\" inizia con vocale, quindi: an."},{"q":"I have ___ dog. ___ dog is very cute.","opts":["a / The","an / A","the / A","a / A"],"correct":0,"expl":"Prima menzione = a; seconda menzione (gia noto) = the."},{"q":"___ sun is very hot today.","opts":["A","An","The","--"],"correct":2,"expl":"Oggetto unico nel contesto: the."},{"q":"He wants to be ___ actor.","opts":["a","an","the","--"],"correct":1,"expl":"\"actor\" inizia con vocale: an."},{"q":"I eat ___ apple every day.","opts":["a","an","the","--"],"correct":1,"expl":"\"apple\" inizia con vocale: an."}],"_id":"0TFzM8kHLz7tneyQ"}
{"title":"The Verb \"To Be\" - Presente","type":"quiz","level":"A1","category":"Grammatica","desc":"Impara a usare il verbo essere in inglese al presente.","points":30,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"She ___ a teacher.","opts":["am","is","are","be"],"correct":1,"expl":"Con she/he/it si usa IS."},{"q":"They ___ my friends.","opts":["is","am","are","be"],"correct":2,"expl":"Con they/we/you si usa ARE."},{"q":"I ___ from Italy.","opts":["is","are","am","be"],"correct":2,"expl":"Con I si usa sempre AM."},{"q":"We ___ happy today.","opts":["is","am","be","are"],"correct":3,"expl":"Con we si usa ARE."},{"q":"\"___ you ready?\" - \"Yes, I ___.\"","opts":["Are / am","Is / are","Am / is","Be / be"],"correct":0,"expl":"Domanda con you: Are; risposta con I: am."}],"_id":"7oWj8Uulr72XkiWc"}
{"title":"Advanced Idioms & Fixed Expressions","type":"quiz","level":"C1","category":"Vocabolario","desc":"Espressioni idiomatiche avanzate per sembrare un madrelingua.","points":85,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"\"Bite the bullet\" significa:","opts":["Fare qualcosa di pericoloso","Sopportare una situazione difficile con coraggio","Fare una scelta rapida","Arrendersi"],"correct":1,"expl":"Bite the bullet = sopportare qualcosa di doloroso con fermezza."},{"q":"\"The ball is in your court\" significa:","opts":["Sei bravo a giocare","Sta a te decidere","E un problema sportivo","Non e una tua responsabilita"],"correct":1,"expl":"The ball is in your court = tocca a te fare la prossima mossa."},{"q":"\"Burn bridges\" significa:","opts":["Distruggere relazioni definitivamente","Fare un grande errore","Lavorare sotto pressione","Viaggiare molto"],"correct":0,"expl":"Burn bridges = rovinare irrimediabilmente un rapporto."},{"q":"\"On the fence\" significa:","opts":["Molto deciso","Indeciso tra due opzioni","Fisicamente su un recinto","Contrario a qualcosa"],"correct":1,"expl":"On the fence = indeciso, non schierato da nessuna parte."},{"q":"\"Let the cat out of the bag\" significa:","opts":["Liberare un animale","Rivelare un segreto","Fare confusione","Perdere il controllo"],"correct":1,"expl":"Let the cat out of the bag = rivelare accidentalmente un segreto."}],"_id":"82mbXT6QX7b0lLj3"}
{"title":"Numbers & Basic Vocabulary","type":"quiz","level":"A1","category":"Vocabolario","desc":"Numeri, colori e oggetti di uso quotidiano.","points":25,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"Come si dice \"rosso\" in inglese?","opts":["Blue","Green","Red","Yellow"],"correct":2,"expl":"Red = rosso."},{"q":"Quante sono \"twelve\"?","opts":["10","11","12","13"],"correct":2,"expl":"Twelve = 12."},{"q":"Come si dice \"libro\" in inglese?","opts":["Pen","Book","Desk","Chair"],"correct":1,"expl":"Book = libro."},{"q":"\"Good morning\" si usa:","opts":["Di sera","Di notte","Di mattina","A pranzo"],"correct":2,"expl":"Good morning = buongiorno (usato la mattina)."},{"q":"Come si chiede \"Come stai?\" in inglese?","opts":["Where are you?","What is your name?","How are you?","Who are you?"],"correct":2,"expl":"How are you? = Come stai?"}],"_id":"B1ssQQFT6xWifLE7"}
{"title":"Subjunctive & Wish Clauses","type":"quiz","level":"C2","category":"Grammatica","desc":"Il congiuntivo e le wish clauses per desideri e rimpianti.","points":100,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"I wish I ___ (speak) Italian fluently.","opts":["speak","spoke","had spoken","would speak"],"correct":1,"expl":"Wish + Past Simple per desideri irrealizzabili al presente."},{"q":"If only she ___ (not say) that! I am so embarrassed.","opts":["did not say","had not said","would not say","has not said"],"correct":1,"expl":"If only + Past Perfect per rimpianti su eventi passati."},{"q":"The committee insists that he ___ present at the meeting.","opts":["is","was","be","were"],"correct":2,"expl":"Mandative subjunctive: after insist/recommend/suggest that -> base form (be)."},{"q":"I would rather you ___ (not tell) anyone about this.","opts":["do not tell","did not tell","had not told","would not tell"],"correct":1,"expl":"I would rather + soggetto + Past Simple per preferenze attuali."},{"q":"It is high time you ___ (make) a decision!","opts":["make","made","had made","will make"],"correct":1,"expl":"It is high time + Past Simple = sarebbe ora che tu facessi."}],"_id":"Hz5WJDbtCIxsHZon"}
{"title":"Past Simple: Regular & Irregular Verbs","type":"quiz","level":"A2","category":"Grammatica","desc":"Il passato semplice: verbi regolari e irregolari piu comuni.","points":50,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"Yesterday she ___ (go) to the supermarket.","opts":["goes","goed","went","gone"],"correct":2,"expl":"Go e irregolare: go -> went."},{"q":"They ___ (play) football last Saturday.","opts":["play","plays","played","plaied"],"correct":2,"expl":"Play e regolare: play -> played."},{"q":"He ___ (not eat) breakfast this morning.","opts":["did not ate","did not eat","does not ate","was not eat"],"correct":1,"expl":"Negativo con did: did not + base form (eat)."},{"q":"___ you ___ (see) that film?","opts":["Did / see","Did / saw","Do / see","Were / see"],"correct":0,"expl":"Domanda al Past Simple: Did + soggetto + base form."},{"q":"She ___ (write) three emails yesterday.","opts":["write","writed","wrote","written"],"correct":2,"expl":"Write e irregolare: write -> wrote."}],"_id":"RcTEa7A4pckTgiMA"}
{"title":"Present Perfect vs Past Simple","type":"quiz","level":"B1","category":"Grammatica","desc":"Quando usare il Present Perfect e quando il Past Simple.","points":60,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"I ___ (never/be) to Japan.","opts":["was never","have never been","never went","never been"],"correct":1,"expl":"Esperienza di vita senza tempo specifico: Present Perfect (have been)."},{"q":"She ___ (finish) her homework an hour ago.","opts":["has finished","finished","finishes","had finished"],"correct":1,"expl":"\"An hour ago\" indica un tempo passato specifico: Past Simple."},{"q":"___ you ever ___ (try) sushi?","opts":["Did / try","Have / tried","Have / try","Did / tried"],"correct":1,"expl":"\"Ever\" con esperienze: Present Perfect: Have you ever tried?"},{"q":"He ___ (live) in London for 5 years. He still lives there now.","opts":["lived","has lived","was living","had lived"],"correct":1,"expl":"Azione iniziata nel passato e ancora in corso: Present Perfect."},{"q":"We ___ (go) to Paris last summer.","opts":["have gone","went","go","have went"],"correct":1,"expl":"\"Last summer\" = tempo passato specifico: Past Simple."}],"_id":"ZU3lK56Id5y3RpYs"}
{"title":"Common Phrasal Verbs: Daily Life","type":"quiz","level":"A2","category":"Vocabolario","desc":"I phrasal verbs piu usati nella vita di tutti i giorni.","points":40,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"\"Wake up\" significa:","opts":["Svegliarsi","Alzarsi dal letto","Andare a dormire","Lavarsi"],"correct":0,"expl":"Wake up = svegliarsi."},{"q":"\"Look after\" significa:","opts":["Guardare dopo","Cercare","Prendersi cura di","Aspettare"],"correct":2,"expl":"Look after = prendersi cura di qualcuno/qualcosa."},{"q":"\"Give up\" significa:","opts":["Dare un regalo","Arrendersi","Alzare la mano","Consegnare"],"correct":1,"expl":"Give up = arrendersi, smettere di fare qualcosa."},{"q":"\"Run out of\" significa:","opts":["Correre fuori","Scappare","Rimanere senza","Esaurire energia"],"correct":2,"expl":"Run out of = rimanere senza qualcosa (es. run out of milk)."},{"q":"\"Turn off\" significa:","opts":["Girare","Spegnere","Accendere","Girare intorno"],"correct":1,"expl":"Turn off = spegnere (luce, tv, telefono)."}],"_id":"ZVempHwHQ6KZG9qo"}
{"title":"Past Perfect: Before & After","type":"quiz","level":"B2","category":"Grammatica","desc":"Usa il Past Perfect per descrivere sequenze di eventi nel passato.","points":75,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"When I arrived, she ___ (leave) already.","opts":["left","has left","had left","was leaving"],"correct":2,"expl":"Had + participio: azione completata prima di un altra azione passata."},{"q":"They ___ (never/see) snow before they moved to Canada.","opts":["have never seen","had never seen","never saw","never seen"],"correct":1,"expl":"Past Perfect per esperienze avvenute prima di un punto nel passato."},{"q":"He was tired because he ___ (work) all night.","opts":["worked","was working","has worked","had been working"],"correct":3,"expl":"Past Perfect Continuous: azione in corso fino a un momento passato."},{"q":"After she ___ (finish) the report, she sent it to her boss.","opts":["finished","has finished","had finished","was finishing"],"correct":2,"expl":"After + Past Perfect indica il primo evento avvenuto."},{"q":"The movie ___ (already/start) when we arrived at the cinema.","opts":["already started","has already started","had already started","was already starting"],"correct":2,"expl":"Past Perfect perche il film era iniziato prima del nostro arrivo."}],"_id":"ZX9TahqoCNqsVHrI"}
{"title":"Present Simple vs Present Continuous","type":"quiz","level":"A2","category":"Grammatica","desc":"Distingui le azioni abituali da quelle in corso in questo momento.","points":45,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"She ___ (work) every day from 9 to 5.","opts":["works","is working","work","worked"],"correct":0,"expl":"\"Every day\" indica abitudine: Present Simple (she works)."},{"q":"Look! He ___ (run) in the park!","opts":["runs","ran","is running","run"],"correct":2,"expl":"\"Look!\" indica un azione in corso: Present Continuous."},{"q":"I ___ (love) pizza.","opts":["am loving","loves","love","loving"],"correct":2,"expl":"I verbi di stato (love, want, know) non si usano al Continuous."},{"q":"They ___ (study) right now for the exam.","opts":["study","are studying","studied","studies"],"correct":1,"expl":"\"Right now\": azione in corso = Present Continuous."},{"q":"He usually ___ (drink) coffee, but today he ___ (drink) tea.","opts":["drinks / is drinking","is drinking / drinks","drink / drink","drinks / drinks"],"correct":0,"expl":"\"Usually\" = abitudine (Simple); \"today\" in contrasto = Continuous."}],"_id":"ZxI76TxsIeZkjU9Y"}
{"title":"Modal Verbs: Can, Could, Should, Must","type":"quiz","level":"B1","category":"Grammatica","desc":"Usa i verbi modali per abilita, consigli e obblighi.","points":60,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"You ___ eat more vegetables. It is healthy.","opts":["must","should","can","could"],"correct":1,"expl":"Should = consiglio (dovresti)."},{"q":"She ___ speak three languages when she was young.","opts":["can","should","could","must"],"correct":2,"expl":"Could = abilita nel passato (poteva / riusciva a)."},{"q":"You ___ wear a seatbelt. It is the law.","opts":["should","can","could","must"],"correct":3,"expl":"Must = obbligo forte (devi assolutamente)."},{"q":"___ you help me with this bag, please?","opts":["Must","Should","Could","Will"],"correct":2,"expl":"Could si usa per richieste educate."},{"q":"He ___ be at the office. His car is outside.","opts":["must","should","cannot","could"],"correct":0,"expl":"Must per deduzione logica forte (deve per forza essere li)."}],"_id":"j9n1xj45KxY027Uv"}
{"title":"Second & Third Conditional","type":"quiz","level":"B2","category":"Grammatica","desc":"Situazioni ipotetiche al presente e rimpianti del passato.","points":80,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"If I ___ (win) the lottery, I would travel the world. (2nd)","opts":["win","will win","won","would win"],"correct":2,"expl":"2 condizionale: IF + Past Simple, would + base form."},{"q":"She would have passed if she ___ (study) harder. (3rd)","opts":["studied","had studied","has studied","would study"],"correct":1,"expl":"3 condizionale: IF + Past Perfect, would have + participio."},{"q":"If he ___ (be) taller, he could play basketball. (2nd)","opts":["is","was / were","would be","has been"],"correct":1,"expl":"Nel 2 condizionale si usa were per tutte le persone (formale)."},{"q":"I ___ (call) you if I had known your number. (3rd)","opts":["called","would call","would have called","had called"],"correct":2,"expl":"3 condizionale main clause: would have + past participle."},{"q":"If she ___ (not miss) the bus, she ___ (be) here now. (mixed)","opts":["had not missed / would be","did not miss / would be","had not missed / would have been","did not miss / would have been"],"correct":0,"expl":"Mixed conditional: IF + Past Perfect -> would + base form (effetto al presente)."}],"_id":"nQbUA7Ph8GRzbqQh"}
{"title":"Business English Essentials","type":"quiz","level":"B2","category":"Business","desc":"Frasi, termini e formule indispensabili per l ambiente professionale.","points":70,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"Come si conclude formalmente una mail in inglese?","opts":["See you later!","Best regards,","Bye!","Cheers! (informal)"],"correct":1,"expl":"\"Best regards\" e la chiusura formale standard. \"Cheers\" e informale."},{"q":"\"To table a discussion\" in UK English significa:","opts":["Iniziare subito una discussione","Mettere un idea da parte","Riportare qualcosa sul tavolo","Concludere un meeting"],"correct":1,"expl":"In UK = posticipare; in USA = discuterne ora. Attenzione al contesto!"},{"q":"\"Per our conversation\" si usa per:","opts":["Salutare qualcuno","Riferirsi a qualcosa gia discusso","Fare una proposta nuova","Concludere un contratto"],"correct":1,"expl":"\"Per our conversation\" richiama qualcosa gia detto in precedenza."},{"q":"Qual e il tono corretto di una mail formale?","opts":["Molto amichevole e informale","Neutro, professionale, chiaro","Con abbreviazioni (asap, lol)","Diretto e brusco"],"correct":1,"expl":"Le mail formali devono essere neutrali, chiare e professionali."},{"q":"\"Could you please send me the report by Friday?\" e un esempio di:","opts":["Ordine diretto","Richiesta educata","Proposta","Scusa"],"correct":1,"expl":"\"Could you please...\" e una richiesta molto educata tipica del business."}],"_id":"ndEY4AzLndPrR63b"}
{"title":"First Conditional: Situazioni Reali","type":"quiz","level":"B1","category":"Grammatica","desc":"Il primo condizionale per eventi possibili nel futuro.","points":55,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"If it ___ (rain) tomorrow, we ___ (stay) at home.","opts":["rains / will stay","will rain / stay","rain / stay","rains / stay"],"correct":0,"expl":"1 condizionale: IF + Present Simple -> will + base form."},{"q":"She ___ (be) happy if she ___ (pass) the exam.","opts":["will be / passes","would be / passed","is / will pass","will be / will pass"],"correct":0,"expl":"IF clause: Present Simple; main clause: will."},{"q":"If you ___ (not study), you ___ (fail).","opts":["do not study / will fail","will not study / fail","do not study / fail","did not study / would fail"],"correct":0,"expl":"Negativo nella IF clause: do not + verb."},{"q":"Unless he ___ (hurry), he ___ (miss) the train.","opts":["hurries / will miss","will hurry / misses","hurry / miss","hurries / misses"],"correct":0,"expl":"\"Unless\" = \"if not\". Unless he hurries = if he does not hurry."},{"q":"What ___ you ___ (do) if you ___ (find) a wallet on the street?","opts":["will / do / find","would / do / found","will / do / will find","do / do / find"],"correct":0,"expl":"1 condizionale: will per la domanda, present simple nella IF."}],"_id":"q7n8B5fQCTaOYSTi"}
{"title":"Passive Voice: All Tenses","type":"quiz","level":"C1","category":"Grammatica","desc":"Il passivo in tutti i tempi verbali principali.","points":90,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"The report ___ (write) by Sarah last week.","opts":["was written","is written","has been written","had written"],"correct":0,"expl":"Past Simple passivo: was/were + past participle."},{"q":"New roads ___ (build) in the city at the moment.","opts":["build","are building","are being built","have been built"],"correct":2,"expl":"Present Continuous passivo: am/is/are + being + past participle."},{"q":"The package ___ (deliver) by tomorrow morning.","opts":["will deliver","will be delivered","is going to deliver","is being delivered"],"correct":1,"expl":"Future passivo: will be + past participle."},{"q":"The problem ___ (solve) before you arrived.","opts":["was solved","had been solved","has been solved","is solved"],"correct":1,"expl":"Past Perfect passivo: had been + past participle."},{"q":"It is believed that he ___ (see) near the airport.","opts":["was seen","has seen","sees","saw"],"correct":0,"expl":"Passivo con \"it is believed/thought/reported that\" + past tense."}],"_id":"zQkyLQlUIYordFTc"}
{"title":"Formal Writing & Discourse Markers","type":"quiz","level":"C2","category":"Business","desc":"Connettivi e segnali discorsivi per la scrittura accademica e formale.","points":100,"createdBy":"system","createdAt":1773089731360,"questions":[{"q":"Quale connettivo introduce una conseguenza?","opts":["However","Furthermore","Consequently","Albeit"],"correct":2,"expl":"Consequently = di conseguenza (introduces a result)."},{"q":"\"Notwithstanding the challenges, they succeeded.\" - Cosa significa \"notwithstanding\"?","opts":["A causa di","Nonostante","Grazie a","Durante"],"correct":1,"expl":"Notwithstanding = nonostante (sinonimo formale di despite)."},{"q":"Quale espressione introduce un controargomento?","opts":["In addition","That is to say","Be that as it may","As a result"],"correct":2,"expl":"\"Be that as it may\" = nonostante cio / comunque sia."},{"q":"\"The findings corroborate the hypothesis.\" - \"Corroborate\" significa:","opts":["Contraddicono","Rafforzano / confermano","Mettono in dubbio","Sostituiscono"],"correct":1,"expl":"Corroborate = rafforzare, confermare con prove aggiuntive."},{"q":"Quale espressione e piu formale?","opts":["Also","Plus","Furthermore","And also"],"correct":2,"expl":"\"Furthermore\" e il connettivo additivo piu formale tra le opzioni."}],"_id":"ztWJGt3FXOpTssq3"}
